1
00:01:18,200 --> 00:01:21,830
[Love Has Fireworks]

2
00:01:22,090 --> 00:01:24,789
[Episode 31]

3
00:01:26,870 --> 00:01:29,190
Didn't you say it yourself
at the venture capital conference

4
00:01:29,190 --> 00:01:31,680
that rural revitalization
is a national strategy?

5
00:01:31,680 --> 00:01:33,650
This is definitely
a new wave of the times,

6
00:01:33,650 --> 00:01:34,200
right?

7
00:01:34,650 --> 00:01:35,880
And its impact

8
00:01:36,120 --> 00:01:37,509
is no less significant than

9
00:01:37,509 --> 00:01:39,350
the Reform and Opening-Up era
my father experienced decades ago.

10
00:01:39,350 --> 00:01:40,990
So sometimes I find myself thinking that

11
00:01:40,990 --> 00:01:41,870
it doesn't really matter

12
00:01:41,870 --> 00:01:43,200
whether Fulaxida

13
00:01:44,430 --> 00:01:45,759
ever makes money or not.

14
00:01:46,590 --> 00:01:48,080
Life is so short.

15
00:01:48,420 --> 00:01:49,900
If I run into a wave this big

16
00:01:49,920 --> 00:01:51,180
and don't even jump in,

17
00:01:51,390 --> 00:01:52,200
wouldn't that mean

18
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:54,600
I've got less guts
than that old man of mine?

19
00:01:54,800 --> 00:01:55,440
True.

20
00:01:55,860 --> 00:01:57,640
And let me tell you something else.

21
00:01:57,640 --> 00:01:58,789
Whether a company

22
00:01:59,060 --> 00:02:00,540
can survive in the end

23
00:02:01,370 --> 00:02:03,700
doesn't depend on how much capital it has.

24
00:02:04,090 --> 00:02:05,420
Anyone can put up money.

25
00:02:05,510 --> 00:02:06,640
What really matters

26
00:02:06,750 --> 00:02:09,550
is the personal ability
of the project initiator.

27
00:02:10,310 --> 00:02:11,640
So what I value most

28
00:02:11,990 --> 00:02:13,050
is you, as a person.

29
00:02:15,090 --> 00:02:16,450
Of course, him too.

30
00:02:17,600 --> 00:02:18,320
2022.

31
00:02:19,370 --> 00:02:21,140
One at a time. One at a time.

32
00:02:22,390 --> 00:02:23,520
Because you two are like me—

33
00:02:23,520 --> 00:02:26,250
sharp enough to spot
the business opportunities

34
00:02:26,390 --> 00:02:29,700
of rural development
in such a restless city.

35
00:02:30,540 --> 00:02:32,579
And for that, I truly admire you.

36
00:02:35,210 --> 00:02:35,890
Yifei,

37
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:36,920
how are you...

38
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:39,020
so good at praising yourself?

39
00:02:39,510 --> 00:02:40,740
Teach me sometime, will you?

40
00:02:40,740 --> 00:02:42,700
See? I said you've got sharp instincts.

41
00:02:42,700 --> 00:02:44,010
But anyway,

42
00:02:44,090 --> 00:02:46,329
we're like-minded people,

43
00:02:47,510 --> 00:02:48,360
right?

44
00:02:49,160 --> 00:02:50,500
Look at this vast land.

45
00:02:51,320 --> 00:02:52,180
What is this?

46
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:55,260
This is wealth bestowed by nature.

47
00:02:58,700 --> 00:02:59,960
But in my opinion,

48
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:01,850
Fulaxida's strength right now

49
00:03:01,870 --> 00:03:03,270
is still far from enough.

50
00:03:03,380 --> 00:03:04,500
Still too slow.

51
00:03:05,140 --> 00:03:07,040
In the future, we must develop this place

52
00:03:07,040 --> 00:03:09,370
into a model zone for modern agriculture.

53
00:03:12,670 --> 00:03:14,200
You want to raise funds now?

54
00:03:14,460 --> 00:03:16,060
Didn't you disagree before?

55
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:19,490
What I disagreed with
was raising dumb money.

56
00:03:19,650 --> 00:03:20,390
Because that kind of money is

57
00:03:20,390 --> 00:03:22,370
as good as burned—
it won't leave you with anything real,

58
00:03:22,370 --> 00:03:23,260
you understand?

59
00:03:23,260 --> 00:03:25,150
What we really need

60
00:03:25,670 --> 00:03:26,780
is smart money—capital that comes

61
00:03:26,780 --> 00:03:29,180
with valuable resources and connections.

62
00:03:29,300 --> 00:03:30,810
That's the kind of money I want.

63
00:03:30,810 --> 00:03:32,210
And the more, the better.

64
00:03:32,730 --> 00:03:34,340
Only that kind of capital

65
00:03:34,370 --> 00:03:36,660
can turn this dream into reality.

66
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:39,390
I get it.

67
00:03:40,040 --> 00:03:42,240
We're going after the right investors.

68
00:03:52,350 --> 00:03:52,950
Exactly.

69
00:03:53,130 --> 00:03:54,560
That's what Yifei said.

70
00:03:54,590 --> 00:03:55,810
He's agreed to raise funding.

71
00:03:55,810 --> 00:03:57,670
It really wasn't easy

72
00:03:57,860 --> 00:03:59,400
to get Mr. Li to budge.

73
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:01,540
Isn't it just smart money?

74
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:03,440
I'll go prepare it now.

75
00:04:03,750 --> 00:04:04,280
Okay.

76
00:04:10,050 --> 00:04:18,410
[Sanglin Group Co., Ltd.]

77
00:04:17,310 --> 00:04:18,010
Alright.

78
00:04:19,010 --> 00:04:20,670
Now the big problem is solved.

79
00:04:21,940 --> 00:04:23,980
Once Fulaxida goes public
through a reverse merger,

80
00:04:23,980 --> 00:04:26,040
the shares I'm holding on your behalf

81
00:04:26,970 --> 00:04:28,700
will multiply dozens of times.

82
00:04:29,660 --> 00:04:31,790
But only if I'm still alive to claim it.

83
00:04:31,910 --> 00:04:33,840
The situation isn't looking good.

84
00:04:34,650 --> 00:04:36,460
I think we need to speed things up

85
00:04:37,230 --> 00:04:39,430
before something unexpected happens.

86
00:04:39,970 --> 00:04:41,630
I've done my best with my part.

87
00:04:42,350 --> 00:04:43,480
The rest is up to you.

88
00:04:44,460 --> 00:04:45,240
Don't worry.

89
00:04:46,350 --> 00:04:48,190
We've been friends for decades.

90
00:04:49,700 --> 00:04:50,760
Just leave it to me.

91
00:04:51,770 --> 00:04:52,230
Come on,

92
00:04:52,840 --> 00:04:53,550
have some water.

93
00:04:53,550 --> 00:04:55,659
[Sanglin Group Co., Ltd.]

94
00:04:56,550 --> 00:04:58,150
I know how you handle things.

95
00:04:59,280 --> 00:05:00,350
But sometimes,

96
00:05:00,620 --> 00:05:02,400
things just don't go as planned.

97
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:04,600
Better to be cautious, don't you think?

98
00:05:20,870 --> 00:05:21,800
Is it connected?

99
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:22,620
Yes!

100
00:05:22,650 --> 00:05:23,560
Is it working?

101
00:05:23,620 --> 00:05:24,380
Yes!

102
00:05:40,180 --> 00:05:43,190
You know, you look just like
a lovesick teenager.

103
00:05:44,730 --> 00:05:46,110
Where's that fire you had

104
00:05:46,110 --> 00:05:47,600
when you were winning over

105
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:48,460
the villagers?

106
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:50,040
Pull yourself together.

107
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:53,710
It's all work.

108
00:05:59,640 --> 00:06:01,070
My wife called me.

109
00:06:02,080 --> 00:06:04,790
Qian Fei didn't even know
you'd come here on a business trip.

110
00:06:04,790 --> 00:06:06,920
What's going on? Trouble in paradise?

111
00:06:09,110 --> 00:06:09,840
Nothing.

112
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:11,020
Nothing at all.

113
00:06:15,170 --> 00:06:15,610
I see.

114
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:17,280
Off to a bad start.

115
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:20,360
What nonsense are you talking about?

116
00:06:20,360 --> 00:06:21,290
What do you know?

117
00:06:23,960 --> 00:06:24,820
Let me tell you,

118
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:28,080
I used to be just like you.

119
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:29,880
Before, with my wife,

120
00:06:29,910 --> 00:06:31,500
I used to just keep everything in my head—

121
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:33,860
thinking it over, imagining things,

122
00:06:33,890 --> 00:06:35,570
blah blah blah, and all that.

123
00:06:36,010 --> 00:06:38,140
But I forgot the most important thing—

124
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:39,670
feeling.

125
00:06:40,770 --> 00:06:43,570
As long as it feels right,
that's all that matters.

126
00:06:44,550 --> 00:06:45,159
I know.

127
00:06:45,250 --> 00:06:47,170
You finance guys always like

128
00:06:47,190 --> 00:06:49,630
calculating your returns and losses,

129
00:06:49,659 --> 00:06:51,720
and planning for every contingency.

130
00:06:52,260 --> 00:06:54,670
But love isn't rational.

131
00:06:54,690 --> 00:06:55,960
It's emotional.

132
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:57,980
And I'll tell you this—

133
00:06:58,220 --> 00:06:59,620
if fate has already planned a relationship

134
00:06:59,620 --> 00:07:00,650
for the two of you,

135
00:07:00,970 --> 00:07:02,390
then as long as your paths cross,

136
00:07:02,390 --> 00:07:03,500
there's no escaping it.

137
00:07:03,500 --> 00:07:06,760
Running all the way out here
still won't make a difference.

138
00:07:09,750 --> 00:07:11,080
So, Mr. Li,

139
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:14,790
you're just
making things harder on yourself.

140
00:07:18,230 --> 00:07:19,330
Keep an eye on things here.

141
00:07:19,330 --> 00:07:20,990
I'll go take a look over there.

142
00:07:36,480 --> 00:07:43,270
♪ What matters to me is what you need ♪

143
00:07:44,470 --> 00:07:50,730
♪ Nothing more, nothing less,
I just hope it's something I can give ♪

144
00:07:48,080 --> 00:07:49,380
Why is it you?

145
00:07:51,450 --> 00:07:57,760
♪ What I cherish is what I have ♪

146
00:07:59,270 --> 00:08:04,930
♪ Every little moment,
I hope you're there with me ♪

147
00:08:06,130 --> 00:08:09,880
♪ Those fairy tales, sweet words,
and declarations of love ♪

148
00:08:11,730 --> 00:08:13,880
♪ Are like fireworks
lighting up the night ♪

149
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:15,160
Cut it out! Let's fulfill the contract.

150
00:08:14,340 --> 00:08:18,540
♪ Truths, lies,
and words said just for show ♪

151
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:18,620
Fulfill the contract.

152
00:08:19,320 --> 00:08:21,040
♪ Feel like I'm walking on cotton ♪

153
00:08:21,470 --> 00:08:25,650
♪ Harsh words, lies,
and words I can't make sense of ♪

154
00:08:26,330 --> 00:08:28,320
♪ Pretentious words wrapped
in glitter and glamour ♪

155
00:08:28,550 --> 00:08:32,909
♪ Dreams, madness,
and the words buried in my heart ♪

156
00:08:33,470 --> 00:08:37,480
♪ Under your fiery eyes ♪

157
00:08:53,060 --> 00:08:59,930
♪ What I dream of is being with you ♪

158
00:09:00,670 --> 00:09:06,770
♪ Hand in hand,
taking life at an easy pace ♪

159
00:09:07,430 --> 00:09:13,760
♪ What I wish for
is something that lasts ♪

160
00:09:15,290 --> 00:09:21,220
♪ Day by day, holding you close
in a life that's simple and true ♪

161
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:26,160
♪ Those fairy tales, sweet words,
and declarations of love ♪

162
00:09:26,660 --> 00:09:30,150
♪ Are like fireworks
lighting up the night ♪

163
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:34,660
♪ Truths, lies,
and words said just for show ♪

164
