♪ Pretentious words wrapped
in glitter and glamour ♪

167
00:09:45,050 --> 00:09:48,960
♪ Dreams, madness,
and the words buried in my heart ♪

168
00:09:49,970 --> 00:09:53,660
♪ Under your fiery eyes ♪

169
00:10:00,220 --> 00:10:03,750
♪ Those fairy tales, sweet words,
and declarations of love ♪

170
00:10:05,190 --> 00:10:08,040
♪ Are like fireworks
lighting up the night ♪

171
00:10:08,700 --> 00:10:14,650
♪ Dreams, madness,
and the words buried in my heart ♪

172
00:10:20,130 --> 00:10:20,860
[Online Q&A]

173
00:10:21,100 --> 00:10:21,880
I used

174
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:23,610
[Fulaxida, well done]

175
00:10:21,880 --> 00:10:23,760
a small camera like this,

176
00:10:23,830 --> 00:10:26,160
so experts could remotely guide him

177
00:10:26,180 --> 00:10:28,400
in treating his son, over several months.

178
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:29,950
The results were excellent!

179
00:10:29,950 --> 00:10:32,840
They're currently in Shanghai
for a follow-up visit

180
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:34,440
and will be back in a few days.

181
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:38,450
-How is that not the same thing?
-It's only been a few days,

182
00:10:38,450 --> 00:10:39,730
-but you've lost weight.
-His son, Xin Ba,

183
00:10:39,730 --> 00:10:41,320
could receive treatment and guidance

184
00:10:41,320 --> 00:10:44,650
from international medical experts
in such a remote place—

185
00:10:45,040 --> 00:10:46,440
what made that possible?

186
00:10:48,590 --> 00:10:50,990
[Xin You]

187
00:10:52,880 --> 00:10:54,120
Xin You,

188
00:10:54,400 --> 00:10:55,640
it's me, Qian Fei.

189
00:10:56,660 --> 00:10:58,990
I just came across a short video
about you.

190
00:10:59,070 --> 00:11:00,600
How are you and Xin Ba doing?

191
00:11:51,680 --> 00:11:53,020
Hello, Xin You.

192
00:11:54,310 --> 00:11:56,520
You saw my message, right?

193
00:11:59,810 --> 00:12:01,930
You're in Shanghai now?

194
00:12:02,970 --> 00:12:04,430
I'm free. Yes, I'm free.

195
00:12:05,470 --> 00:12:07,270
Okay, let's meet tomorrow then.

196
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:09,730
Okay, see you tomorrow.

197
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:31,990
I'm so sorry

198
00:12:32,100 --> 00:12:34,700
you had to stay
and play with  my son for so long.

199
00:12:34,830 --> 00:12:35,830
Not at all.

200
00:12:35,830 --> 00:12:37,310
Seeing how well
he's responding to the treatment,

201
00:12:37,310 --> 00:12:38,570
I couldn't be happier.

202
00:12:39,740 --> 00:12:40,880
We should thank Yifei.

203
00:12:40,880 --> 00:12:41,740
After you left,

204
00:12:41,790 --> 00:12:44,550
specialists continued
treating Xin Ba online.

205
00:12:44,570 --> 00:12:47,710
This trip here is for him
to meet the specialists in person.

206
00:12:47,710 --> 00:12:50,300
They said
Xin Ba's social communication skills

207
00:12:50,300 --> 00:12:51,300
have improved

208
00:12:51,430 --> 00:12:53,410
and are now on par with kids his age.

209
00:12:53,520 --> 00:12:54,580
That's wonderful.

210
00:12:54,590 --> 00:12:55,240
That means

211
00:12:55,240 --> 00:12:57,140
he can make more friends from now on.

212
00:12:57,140 --> 00:12:58,550
I remember he and Ji

213
00:12:58,550 --> 00:13:00,600
had a falling out once.

214
00:13:00,820 --> 00:13:01,380
Yes.

215
00:13:01,660 --> 00:13:03,320
And there's even better news.

216
00:13:04,060 --> 00:13:05,780
Yifei's company, Fulaxida,

217
00:13:05,880 --> 00:13:07,100
has chosen our county

218
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:09,060
as the site for its pilot farm.

219
00:13:09,090 --> 00:13:10,440
It's boosted the economy

220
00:13:10,440 --> 00:13:11,640
of our entire county.

221
00:13:11,950 --> 00:13:12,980
Next time you come,

222
00:13:12,980 --> 00:13:14,680
you won't have to worry about
your car breaking down

223
00:13:14,680 --> 00:13:15,890
on those remote mountain roads—

224
00:13:15,890 --> 00:13:18,280
there are logistics trucks
coming and going every day now.

225
00:13:18,280 --> 00:13:21,120
Fulaxida is Li Yifei's company?

226
00:13:21,980 --> 00:13:24,030
Well, it's just a side venture for him.

227
00:13:24,030 --> 00:13:24,880
But

228
00:13:24,940 --> 00:13:27,950
he must be a major shareholder
of Fulaxida.

229
00:13:32,180 --> 00:13:32,650
Look.

230
00:13:33,630 --> 00:13:34,680
This was taken before we left.

231
00:13:34,680 --> 00:13:37,080
Yifei brought
his new technology consultants

232
00:13:37,080 --> 00:13:37,940
to our village.

233
00:13:38,650 --> 00:13:41,100
He said they were going to
develop some kind of livestream app

234
00:13:41,100 --> 00:13:43,460
for cattle, sheep, and so on.

235
00:13:43,490 --> 00:13:45,290
It sounded pretty interesting.

236
00:13:46,670 --> 00:13:49,120
I heard Yifei's company
has a technical partnership

237
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:50,360
with Mr. Lu's company.

238
00:13:50,360 --> 00:13:51,740
That way, consumers

239
00:13:51,760 --> 00:13:53,470
can log into the app directly

240
00:13:53,500 --> 00:13:56,500
to check the agricultural products
they've ordered—

241
00:13:57,190 --> 00:13:57,890
from the moment of

242
00:13:57,890 --> 00:14:00,640
planting or birth,
through every stage of growth,

243
00:14:00,640 --> 00:14:02,570
all the way to their dining table.

244
00:14:02,630 --> 00:14:03,890
Isn't that wonderful?

245
00:14:04,040 --> 00:14:05,570
He's so business-savvy.

246
00:14:05,940 --> 00:14:08,020
My God. He's done so much all this time

247
00:14:08,050 --> 00:14:09,450
without me even knowing.

248
00:14:10,700 --> 00:14:11,890
In the same amount of time,

249
00:14:11,890 --> 00:14:13,210
with all my effort,

250
00:14:13,240 --> 00:14:15,120
I only went from one to ten,

251
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:17,180
while he went from ten to fifty.

252
00:14:17,210 --> 00:14:18,420
Looking at it that way,

253
00:14:18,420 --> 00:14:19,750
you should be proud too.

254
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:21,610
In the same amount of time,

255
00:14:21,610 --> 00:14:22,950
you improved tenfold,

256
00:14:22,990 --> 00:14:24,720
and he only improved fivefold.

257
00:14:25,430 --> 00:14:26,260
As for my son,

258
00:14:26,710 --> 00:14:28,950
he went from zero to one.

259
00:14:28,970 --> 00:14:30,250
Even that small step

260
00:14:30,620 --> 00:14:32,960
already feels like a great miracle to me.

261
00:14:32,990 --> 00:14:34,140
Fei!

262
00:14:34,350 --> 00:14:34,800
Xin Ba.

263
00:14:34,820 --> 00:14:35,310
Xin Ba.

264
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:36,050
I'm happy.

265
00:14:36,160 --> 00:14:37,760
-Happy?
-Say goodbye to Fei.

266
00:14:37,870 --> 00:14:38,890
We're going back.

267
00:14:39,370 --> 00:14:40,640
You're leaving already?

268
00:14:40,640 --> 00:14:42,010
He has to get back to school.

269
00:14:42,010 --> 00:14:43,660
Our flight is tonight.

270
00:14:43,990 --> 00:14:44,840
And we hope

271
00:14:45,590 --> 00:14:47,200
you'll come visit us sometime.

272
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:47,930
Definitely.

273
00:14:48,240 --> 00:14:49,470
I'll see you off.

274
00:14:49,860 --> 00:14:50,220
Okay.

275
00:14:59,170 --> 00:14:59,650
[Anti-Scam Center Alert: If you
receive messages on short video platforms]

276
00:14:59,680 --> 00:15:00,150
[or instant messaging apps like iMessage
from someone claiming to be a leader,]

277
00:15:00,180 --> 00:15:00,470
[or a contact who says they've changed
their phone number, please stay alert.]

278
00:15:00,490 --> 00:15:00,880
[Verify their identity immediately
to avoid fraud.]

279
00:15:04,880 --> 00:15:08,010
It's been so many days,
and he hasn't contacted me at all.

280
00:15:30,260 --> 00:15:32,400
[Pretentious Li]

281
00:15:40,880 --> 00:15:41,050
[WeChat]

282
00:15:42,040 --> 00:15:45,010
[Another fruitful day]

283
00:15:57,650 --> 00:15:59,070
It feels like everyone

284
00:15:59,710 --> 00:16:01,240
is revolving around you,

285
00:16:02,920 --> 00:16:03,890
except me.

286
00:16:05,870 --> 00:16:08,130
Like I'm the one being kept at a distance.

287
00:16:46,170 --> 00:16:47,410
Hello.

288
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:48,950
Honey!

289
00:16:52,410 --> 00:16:54,210
You look so silly, but handsome.

290
00:16:54,290 --> 00:16:57,100
[Microphone On] [Speaker On] [Camera On]

291
00:16:54,560 --> 00:16:55,400
You're the silly one.

292
00:16:55,400 --> 00:16:57,600
I came to the greenhouse
to adjust the equipment.

293
00:16:57,600 --> 00:16:58,660
So you missed me?

294
00:16:59,750 --> 00:17:00,880
I missed you so much.

295
00:17:02,650 --> 00:17:04,180
Let me tell you some gossip.

296
00:17:04,190 --> 00:17:04,950
What is it?

297
00:17:05,369 --> 00:17:06,130
Li Yifei

298
00:17:06,990 --> 00:17:07,839
came all the way here,

299
00:17:07,839 --> 00:17:09,510
and he's been completely lovesick
over Qian Fei.

300
00:17:09,510 --> 00:17:11,240
But he doesn't even realize it.

301
00:17:13,329 --> 00:17:14,859
So that's how it is.

302
00:17:15,770 --> 00:17:16,950
I'm about to meet up with Fei.

303
00:17:16,950 --> 00:17:18,319
Should I tell her?

304
00:17:17,579 --> 00:17:21,119
[Microphone On] [Speaker On] [Camera On]

305
00:17:18,750 --> 00:17:19,599
No, no, no.

306
00:17:20,030 --> 00:17:21,560
Don't get involved in this.

307
00:17:21,760 --> 00:17:23,319
Just let things happen naturally
between them.

308
00:17:23,319 --> 00:17:26,780
If outsiders get involved,
it'll put a lot of pressure on them.

309
00:17:27,099 --> 00:17:28,140
Alright then.

310
00:17:28,840 --> 00:17:30,320
Trust me, I'm right.

311
00:17:31,270 --> 00:17:32,470
Okay, I'm hanging up.

312
00:17:38,940 --> 00:17:42,740
So I had to put down my phone every day,

313
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:45,350
cook alone,

314
00:17:46,470 --> 00:17:48,560
check job listings alone,

315
00:17:49,510 --> 00:17:51,160
do chores alone,

316
00:17:51,750 --> 00:17:54,120
and say goodnight to the wall.

317
00:17:56,080 --> 00:17:57,710
Then you felt lonely

318
00:17:57,730 --> 00:17:59,120
and asked me out.

319
00:18:04,930 --> 00:18:06,220
Actually...

320
00:18:09,490 --> 00:18:11,140
You two are really interesting.

321
00:18:11,140 --> 00:18:11,820
You...

322
00:18:13,640 --> 00:18:14,190
He...

323
00:18:14,470 --> 00:18:16,030
Me, him, me, him... Come on.

324
00:18:16,080 --> 00:18:18,010
Can you just finish your sentence?

325
00:18:18,060 --> 00:18:20,480
Don't you think you're acting like

326
00:18:21,270 --> 00:18:22,030
someone who's either in love

327
00:18:22,030 --> 00:18:23,960
or has just had their heart broken?

328
00:18:25,190 --> 00:18:26,330
Why do you say that?

329
00:18:27,690 --> 00:18:30,030
Because I'm picking up a different

330
00:18:30,060 --> 00:18:32,260
vibe from you.

331
00:18:32,750 --> 00:18:34,570
What are you, a dog?

332
00:18:36,660 --> 00:18:39,110
I just feel so embarrassed.

333
00:18:39,600 --> 00:18:40,510
I thought

334
00:18:40,990 --> 00:18:43,420
that kiss between us was just a dream.

335
00:18:44,080 --> 00:18:45,580
Now he's avoiding me,

336
00:18:45,980 --> 00:18:49,510
using a business trip as an excuse
to run as far away as possible.

337
00:18:49,720 --> 00:18:51,510
How am I supposed to get out of

338
00:18:52,080 --> 00:18:53,610
such an awkward situation?

339
00:18:54,760 --> 00:18:55,590
Fei,

340
00:18:56,230 --> 00:18:57,180
honestly,

341
00:18:57,490 --> 00:18:59,120
I'm certain you like him.

342
00:19:03,890 --> 00:19:05,490
I've never thought about it.

343
00:19:06,320 --> 00:19:07,650
Never thought about it?

344
00:19:07,950 --> 00:19:08,810
What about now?

345
00:19:10,960 --> 00:19:11,960
Let me think then.

346
00:19:15,860 --> 00:19:18,590
I wouldn't exactly call it "liking" him.

347
00:19:19,060 --> 00:19:20,210
It's just that...

348
00:19:21,030 --> 00:19:23,010
it's pretty boring without him around.

349
00:19:23,010 --> 00:19:25,610
Maybe I've just gotten used to
cooking for him.

350
00:19:26,750 --> 00:19:27,510
Okay then.

351
00:19:28,810 --> 00:19:30,940
Let me help you sort out your thoughts.

352
00:19:31,710 --> 00:19:34,070
Let's set aside
whether you like him or not for now.

353
00:19:34,070 --> 00:19:35,910
First, you have to admit

354
00:19:36,200 --> 00:19:38,440
that he's not from the same world as us.

355
00:19:39,250 --> 00:19:41,240
Look at what he eats, wears,
and plays with—

356
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:42,770
none of it's in your league.

357
00:19:42,790 --> 00:19:45,280
Then what league is he in,
and what league am I in?

358
00:19:45,280 --> 00:19:45,910
You?

359
00:19:45,940 --> 00:19:47,180
Needless to say,

360
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:49,270
you're in the grassroots league.

361
00:19:50,760 --> 00:19:51,840
But him?

362
00:19:52,150 --> 00:19:54,060
He runs in the rich,
handsome, elite league.

363
00:19:54,060 --> 00:19:56,730
People like him
have countless ways to make money.

364
00:19:56,730 --> 00:19:57,770
Lu Ze told me

365
00:19:57,800 --> 00:19:59,320
that Li Yifei invested a huge amount

366
00:19:59,320 --> 00:20:00,580
in Fulaxida.

367
00:20:01,070 --> 00:20:02,540
He sold his house.

368
00:20:02,660 --> 00:20:04,080
Went all in.

369
00:20:04,160 --> 00:20:06,490
Tens of millions invested just like that.

370
00:20:06,920 --> 00:20:08,610
I heard

371
00:20:08,820 --> 00:20:11,350
that the house was
actually bought by his dad.

372
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,990
Later, the house appreciated in value,

373
00:20:13,990 --> 00:20:15,670
so he sold it

374
00:20:15,950 --> 00:20:17,280
and invested the money.

375
00:20:17,340 --> 00:20:20,800
Now, isn't he so broke that he has to
share an apartment with me?

376
00:20:21,300 --> 00:20:22,450
Let's not talk about him anymore.

377
00:20:22,450 --> 00:20:24,090
Let's talk about your Lu Ze.

378
00:20:24,390 --> 00:20:27,040
He suddenly switched careers
to go into agriculture.

379
00:20:27,040 --> 00:20:29,800
How did you manage to
talk yourself into supporting him?

380
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:30,560
Qian Fei,

381
00:20:31,060 --> 00:20:32,730
can you focus a bit?

382
00:20:32,760 --> 00:20:34,710
Where's your attention
wandering off to now?

383
00:20:34,710 --> 00:20:36,190
I'm talking to you about Li Yifei,

384
00:20:36,190 --> 00:20:38,920
and now you're bringing up
Lu Ze and agriculture?

385
00:20:39,810 --> 00:20:42,010
Haven't you noticed you always do this?

386
00:20:42,090 --> 00:20:44,620
Whenever the conversation gets to
what you really care about,

387
00:20:44,620 --> 00:20:45,950
you change the subject.

388
00:20:58,710 --> 00:21:00,970
I don't know what's going on with you two.

389
00:21:01,030 --> 00:21:01,950
Anyway, I think

390
00:21:01,950 --> 00:21:03,450
you should just take it one step at a time

391
00:21:03,450 --> 00:21:05,180
and leave everything to time.

392
00:21:06,530 --> 00:21:07,530
Wait and see.

393
00:21:08,940 --> 00:21:09,820
I'll listen to you.

394
00:21:09,820 --> 00:21:12,280
Wait and see,
and let nature take its course.

395
00:21:13,180 --> 00:21:13,780
Thank you.

396
00:21:17,060 --> 00:21:19,180
Oh, right.
Our class monitor called and said

397
00:21:19,180 --> 00:21:21,920
Saturday is
the fifth-anniversary class reunion.

398
00:21:21,920 --> 00:21:22,900
Our student affairs counselor
will be there too.

399
00:21:22,900 --> 00:21:24,150
He asked whether everyone could make it.

400
00:21:24,150 --> 00:21:26,280
No problem. I'll definitely be there.

401
00:21:27,490 --> 00:21:29,970
But I think
he must have also called Wang Ruohai.

402
00:21:29,970 --> 00:21:32,430
If he goes too, will you...

403
00:21:33,060 --> 00:21:35,100
Will I what? Of course I won't.

404
00:21:35,130 --> 00:21:36,270
I worked with him at Shanlifang

405
00:21:36,270 --> 00:21:37,380
for quite some time.

406
00:21:37,380 --> 00:21:38,100
You forgot?

407
00:21:39,430 --> 00:21:40,240
That's good.

408
00:21:40,270 --> 00:21:42,430
Anyway, I'll be out of town that day,

409
00:21:42,450 --> 00:21:44,020
so I won't make a special trip back.

410
00:21:44,020 --> 00:21:45,800
Say hello to everyone for me.

411
00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:47,880
You're not going?

412
00:21:48,560 --> 00:21:49,050
Then...

413
00:21:49,600 --> 00:21:50,380
If you're not going,

414
00:21:50,380 --> 00:21:51,830
won't I be alone?

415
00:21:51,860 --> 00:21:54,340
Dealing with Wang Ruohai all by myself?

416
00:21:54,990 --> 00:21:56,920
Why would you have to deal with him?

417
00:21:57,440 --> 00:21:58,230
Listen,

418
00:21:58,810 --> 00:22:00,740
if he tries to get close to you,

419
00:22:00,760 --> 00:22:01,840
it's easy to handle.

420
00:22:01,840 --> 00:22:03,500
Just slap him across the face.

421
00:22:05,540 --> 00:22:06,800
Problem solved.

422
00:22:06,920 --> 00:22:09,020
Your project is really good.

423
00:22:09,840 --> 00:22:12,080
Nowadays, young people in the villages
have all gone out to work.

424
00:22:12,080 --> 00:22:13,280
In our village alone,

425
00:22:13,480 --> 00:22:14,320
there's

426
00:22:14,490 --> 00:22:16,470
a huge amount of farmland lying idle.

427
00:22:16,470 --> 00:22:17,880
If you can use it

428
00:22:17,900 --> 00:22:20,390
for pilot fields
and agricultural development,

429
00:22:20,390 --> 00:22:21,760
helping farmers increase their income,

430
00:22:21,760 --> 00:22:23,860
that would truly be a tremendous service
to the community.

431
00:22:23,860 --> 00:22:25,150
Village Chief, rest assured.

432
00:22:25,150 --> 00:22:26,910
The whole purpose of this project

433
00:22:26,910 --> 00:22:29,640
is to increase
the overall income of the farmers.

434
00:22:30,250 --> 00:22:31,330
I believe that.

435
00:22:31,530 --> 00:22:32,220
How is it?

436
00:22:34,040 --> 00:22:34,990
It's Mr. Sang.

437
00:22:37,430 --> 00:22:39,590
Look, those plots over there
and over there.

438
00:22:39,590 --> 00:22:41,700
They need a bit more water
and are very fertile.

439
00:22:41,700 --> 00:22:42,260
Yes.

440
00:22:42,280 --> 00:22:43,520
It's all excellent farmland.

441
00:22:43,520 --> 00:22:43,940
Yes.

442
00:22:54,340 --> 00:22:56,540
Yifei, I really have to push you on this.

443
00:22:56,920 --> 00:22:59,050
The farmers out there are all waiting.

444
00:23:01,360 --> 00:23:02,960
You mean the financing, right?

445
00:23:02,960 --> 00:23:03,630
Yes.

446
00:23:04,270 --> 00:23:05,800
Didn't you say a few days ago

447
00:23:06,110 --> 00:23:08,370
that we should start further financing?

448
00:23:08,860 --> 00:23:09,870
Are you now...

449
00:23:09,950 --> 00:23:10,600
Ma Li,

450
00:23:11,040 --> 00:23:13,570
I still think
it's too early to raise funding.

451
00:23:13,990 --> 00:23:14,620
No, Yifei.

452
00:23:17,980 --> 00:23:19,160
What do you mean?

453
00:23:19,710 --> 00:23:21,080
You keep flip-flopping—

454
00:23:21,080 --> 00:23:22,450
saying yes to financing one moment
and no the next.

455
00:23:22,450 --> 00:23:24,180
What are you thinking exactly?

456
00:23:25,700 --> 00:23:27,430
The person you met with a few days ago

457
00:23:27,430 --> 00:23:28,590
was Mr. Sang, wasn't it?

458
00:23:28,590 --> 00:23:29,080
Yeah.

459
00:23:29,640 --> 00:23:30,900
Was there anyone else?

460
00:23:31,240 --> 00:23:32,530
And Mr. Liao Jinshan.

461
00:23:33,630 --> 00:23:35,410
Li Yifei, just say what you want to say.

462
00:23:35,410 --> 00:23:37,640
Why does this feel like an interrogation?

463
00:23:37,640 --> 00:23:39,230
Don't meet with Mr. Sang anymore.

464
00:23:39,230 --> 00:23:41,160
You can't tell who's trustworthy.

465
00:23:41,920 --> 00:23:43,360
You're going too far.

466
00:23:43,380 --> 00:23:45,130
Wasn't Mr. Sang introduced to us

467
00:23:45,130 --> 00:23:45,910
through your connections?

468
00:23:45,910 --> 00:23:46,920
If you're denying him now,

469
00:23:46,920 --> 00:23:47,990
you're denying yourself.

470
00:23:47,990 --> 00:23:49,850
I admit I misjudged him this time.

471
00:23:54,540 --> 00:23:56,670
But this time, I'm absolutely certain

472
00:23:57,350 --> 00:23:59,840
that Mr. Sang approached Fulaxida
with an agenda

473
00:23:59,840 --> 00:24:01,240
from the very beginning.

474
00:24:03,830 --> 00:24:05,510
I don't know why you say that.

475
00:24:05,650 --> 00:24:08,080
Maybe you have
your own reasons and judgment.

476
00:24:08,080 --> 00:24:09,410
But what I want to say is,

477
00:24:09,850 --> 00:24:11,240
no matter what you've heard,

478
00:24:11,240 --> 00:24:12,470
when the farmers caused trouble
a few days ago,

479
00:24:12,470 --> 00:24:13,580
if it hadn't been for Mr. Sang,

480
00:24:13,580 --> 00:24:15,100
you and your silver tongue alone

481
00:24:15,100 --> 00:24:15,980
might not have been enough to handle it.

482
00:24:15,980 --> 00:24:16,870
I know what you mean.

483
00:24:16,870 --> 00:24:18,320
You're saying Mr. Sang
paid off those farmers,

484
00:24:18,320 --> 00:24:19,270
and that's why they agreed

485
00:24:19,270 --> 00:24:23,470
-to cooperate with our project, right?
-Yeah. Since you know all that, why…

486
00:24:24,300 --> 00:24:24,890
Ma Li.

487
00:24:26,190 --> 00:24:28,250
Do you know that the farmers' protest

488
00:24:29,070 --> 00:24:31,800
was arranged by Mr. Sang
from the very beginning?

489
00:24:57,230 --> 00:24:58,010
Mr. Liao,

490
00:24:58,260 --> 00:25:00,860
you're here.
Why didn't you call me in advance?

491
00:25:01,620 --> 00:25:02,820
Let's talk in the car.

492
00:25:04,560 --> 00:25:06,490
I'm just about to head to a meeting.

493
00:25:37,760 --> 00:25:39,890
[Information on the Weibo account "0.33"]

494
00:25:40,570 --> 00:25:42,370
Mr. Sang, your acting is superb.

495
00:25:42,470 --> 00:25:44,270
That was a well-executed setup.

496
00:25:45,190 --> 00:25:46,660
[Information on the Weibo account "0.33"]

497
00:25:47,190 --> 00:25:47,830
Mr. Liao,

498
00:25:47,860 --> 00:25:51,120
here's the information
we dug up on the Weibo account 0.33.

499
00:26:04,600 --> 00:26:07,360
Mr. Liao, you're indeed
a veteran businessman—

500
00:26:08,150 --> 00:26:09,270
moving this fast.

501
00:26:11,990 --> 00:26:12,920
What do you mean?

502
00:26:16,340 --> 00:26:17,080
Hello.

503
00:26:18,330 --> 00:26:19,950
I'll be at the airport in an hour.

504
00:26:19,950 --> 00:26:20,750
Help me compile all the cases

505
00:26:20,750 --> 00:26:22,030
from the past 10 years
at Zhizhong Investment

506
00:26:22,030 --> 00:26:23,430
where shareholders

507
00:26:23,430 --> 00:26:26,080
were removed mid-project,

508
00:26:26,400 --> 00:26:27,250
and send them to me.

509
00:26:27,250 --> 00:26:28,730
No problem. Piece of cake.

510
00:26:29,190 --> 00:26:30,790
I'll contact you when I land.

511
00:26:40,940 --> 00:26:41,950
[Summary of Materials]

512
00:26:41,980 --> 00:26:43,230
[on the Mid-Project Removal of Shareholders
in the Zhizhong Investment Project Team]

513
00:27:28,960 --> 00:27:30,930
[Qian Fei]

514
00:27:34,170 --> 00:27:35,870
[Dear passengers, your flight CY3357]

515
00:27:35,890 --> 00:27:36,970
[is expected to depart
in approximately 90 minutes.]

516
00:27:36,990 --> 00:27:38,010
[Please arrange your schedule accordingly]

517
00:27:38,040 --> 00:27:39,850
[to avoid missing your flight.
We wish you a pleasant journey.]

518
00:28:41,870 --> 00:28:42,730
Class Monitor.

519
00:28:45,390 --> 00:28:46,090
Qian Fei?

520
00:28:48,150 --> 00:28:49,280
You're Qian Fei?

521
00:28:50,640 --> 00:28:51,670
Oh my gosh!

522
00:28:52,150 --> 00:28:53,230
Did you get plastic surgery or something?

523
00:28:53,230 --> 00:28:54,530
How did you become t-this gorgeous?

524
00:28:54,530 --> 00:28:55,820
What do you mean, plastic surgery?

525
00:28:55,820 --> 00:28:58,080
Even if I wanted to, I couldn't afford it.

526
00:28:59,710 --> 00:29:01,080
Stop staring at me.

527
00:29:01,080 --> 00:29:01,840
Besides, if I'd really had work done,

528
00:29:01,840 --> 00:29:03,840
you wouldn't be able to tell anyway.

529
00:29:05,080 --> 00:29:06,160
This reunion's

530
00:29:06,160 --> 00:29:07,880
been eye-opening for me.

531
00:29:08,250 --> 00:29:10,030
Everyone's done well for themselves,

532
00:29:10,030 --> 00:29:11,600
especially Wang Ruohai.

533
00:29:12,130 --> 00:29:13,330
But after seeing you,

534
00:29:13,700 --> 00:29:14,760
I can already tell—

535
00:29:14,970 --> 00:29:16,640
you're going to be the biggest surprise

536
00:29:16,640 --> 00:29:17,770
of the night.

537
00:29:17,860 --> 00:29:18,790
No contest.

538
00:29:21,660 --> 00:29:23,940
Don't just stand there.
Come on. We've been waiting for you.

539
00:29:23,940 --> 00:29:24,470
Let's go.

540
00:29:28,680 --> 00:29:29,470
Wait a moment before going in.

541
00:29:29,470 --> 00:29:30,700
Wait here.

542
00:29:32,160 --> 00:29:32,920
Everyone!

543
00:29:33,990 --> 00:29:34,640
Everyone,

544
00:29:34,790 --> 00:29:37,720
open your eyes wide
and take a good look at who's here!

545
00:29:39,210 --> 00:29:40,040
Come in.

546
00:29:40,510 --> 00:29:41,510
Hello, everyone.

547
00:29:42,840 --> 00:29:44,320
Isn't this Qian Fei?

548
00:29:44,320 --> 00:29:45,160
Yes, Qian Fei!

549
00:29:45,510 --> 00:29:46,570
Hello, Professor.

550
00:29:47,410 --> 00:29:48,130
Sit, sit.

551
00:29:48,540 --> 00:29:50,510
I haven't seen her for a long time.

552
00:29:53,400 --> 00:29:55,950
Qian Fei, come on, sit.

553
00:29:58,110 --> 00:29:59,180
So? So?

554
00:29:59,880 --> 00:30:02,640
-Let's eat. Come on.
-Come on, let's dig in.

555
00:30:04,340 --> 00:30:05,550
Come on, let's eat.

556
00:30:05,640 --> 00:30:07,440
Eat up. The food's getting cold.

557
00:30:08,530 --> 00:30:09,770
Well, everyone.

558
00:30:10,640 --> 00:30:11,400
Every year,

559
00:30:11,550 --> 00:30:14,310
seeing all of you again

560
00:30:14,890 --> 00:30:17,700
brings me so much joy.

561
00:30:18,120 --> 00:30:18,800
We only

562
00:30:19,150 --> 00:30:21,720
had one couple in our whole class,

563
00:30:22,950 --> 00:30:24,950
so I hope the two of you

564
00:30:25,170 --> 00:30:26,460
stay together forever.

565
00:30:26,460 --> 00:30:28,190
Professor Zhang, your information
is seriously out of date.

566
00:30:28,190 --> 00:30:29,190
The two of them...

567
00:30:29,300 --> 00:30:31,760
Professor Zhang, you're absolutely right.

568
00:30:31,850 --> 00:30:32,880
Looking back now,

569
00:30:33,030 --> 00:30:34,030
our college days

570
00:30:34,360 --> 00:30:36,330
really were wonderful.

571
00:30:38,570 --> 00:30:39,710
Back then, the love

572
00:30:39,960 --> 00:30:41,150
was just pure love.

573
00:30:41,710 --> 00:30:43,710
As long as you were
looking at the person you loved,

574
00:30:43,710 --> 00:30:45,210
you could do nothing all day

575
00:30:45,210 --> 00:30:47,540
and still smile foolishly the whole time.

576
00:30:49,840 --> 00:30:50,710
Well, Ruohai,

577
00:30:50,960 --> 00:30:52,030
are you trying to be a poet now?

578
00:30:52,030 --> 00:30:53,060
Yeah!

579
00:30:54,380 --> 00:30:55,140
Good! Good!

580
00:30:55,480 --> 00:30:58,310
Well, that reminds me of back then too—

581
00:30:58,330 --> 00:30:59,810
also at our university—

582
00:31:00,180 --> 00:31:01,550
when I met my wife.

583
00:31:02,160 --> 00:31:03,690
She was wearing a red dress,

584
00:31:03,840 --> 00:31:05,640
standing by a tree.

585
00:31:06,340 --> 00:31:09,090
[Wang Ruohai seems kinda weird today.]

586
00:31:07,010 --> 00:31:09,240
At that moment, I remember thinking,

587
00:31:10,540 --> 00:31:12,540
"How could this possibly be winter?

588
00:31:12,760 --> 00:31:14,200
Spring has arrived."

589
00:31:16,630 --> 00:31:17,980
Spring has arrived.

590
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:19,870
M-My biggest regret

591
00:31:20,030 --> 00:31:20,840
about my college years

592
00:31:20,840 --> 00:31:23,120
is never having had
a passionate, all-out romance.

593
00:31:23,120 --> 00:31:24,780
So, to make up for that regret,

594
00:31:24,790 --> 00:31:26,620
I've decided to marry a classmate.

595
00:31:25,060 --> 00:31:25,730
[That bastard didn't
do anything to you, did he?]

596
00:31:25,760 --> 00:31:26,440
[No, he didn't. It's just…]

597
00:31:26,470 --> 00:31:27,490
[Anyway, he seems to regret it
and wants to get back together.]

598
00:31:27,880 --> 00:31:28,510
Mei!

599
00:31:29,800 --> 00:31:32,030
We're going to relive our youth together!

600
00:31:32,030 --> 00:31:33,190
They are getting married?

601
00:31:33,190 --> 00:31:34,490
You even kept it a secret from us, huh?

602
00:31:34,490 --> 00:31:35,460
You hid it so well.

603
00:31:35,460 --> 00:31:36,360
You really hid it well.

604
00:31:36,360 --> 00:31:38,270
W-We'd like to toast everyone.

605
00:31:38,970 --> 00:31:39,630
Come on.

606
00:31:39,660 --> 00:31:40,030
Come on.

607
00:31:40,030 --> 00:31:40,850
Congratulations.

608
00:31:40,850 --> 00:31:42,850
To our friendship—cheers!

609
00:31:42,920 --> 00:31:44,060
Cheers!

610
00:31:44,080 --> 00:31:45,010
Come on, come on.

611
00:31:51,380 --> 00:31:52,840
Don't drink too much. Sit.

612
00:31:53,350 --> 00:31:54,380
Fei.

613
00:31:54,610 --> 00:31:57,340
Is there really no chance
for you and Wang Ruohai?

614
00:31:57,560 --> 00:31:58,420
I can see Wang Ruohai

615
00:31:58,420 --> 00:32:00,050
looking at you so affectionately.

616
00:32:00,050 --> 00:32:02,030
He's clearly trying to
get back together with you.

617
00:32:02,030 --> 00:32:03,300
Impossible.

618
00:32:03,320 --> 00:32:04,560
Look at Mr. Wang now,

619
00:32:04,590 --> 00:32:05,830
-he's way out of my league.
-Well, Ruohai,

620
00:32:05,830 --> 00:32:07,290
you're doing the best out of all of us.

621
00:32:07,290 --> 00:32:08,920
I heard that

622
00:32:09,430 --> 00:32:11,940
after he broke up with that rich girl,

623
00:32:11,960 --> 00:32:14,220
he landed a job at an even bigger company.

624
00:32:14,770 --> 00:32:17,350
He's even paying for tonight's dinner.

625
00:32:21,320 --> 00:32:22,800
Mei, Mei.

626
00:32:23,050 --> 00:32:24,580
Let's toast to our teacher.

627
00:32:28,230 --> 00:32:31,230
Professor Zhang
really took good care of us back then.

628
00:32:35,540 --> 00:32:36,270
Come on, cheers.

629
00:32:36,270 --> 00:32:37,300
Raise your glasses!

630
00:32:37,300 --> 00:32:38,450
I remember this

631
00:32:39,340 --> 00:32:40,740
used to be your favorite.

632
00:32:42,040 --> 00:32:42,840
Thank you.

633
00:32:43,410 --> 00:32:45,140
I heard you're treating today.

634
00:32:45,620 --> 00:32:47,480
Seeing how lavish this spread is,

635
00:32:47,670 --> 00:32:49,270
things really have changed.

636
00:32:49,960 --> 00:32:50,830
No, no.

637
00:32:52,160 --> 00:32:53,910
It's just that, thinking back,

638
00:32:54,210 --> 00:32:55,130
I never took you

639
00:32:56,660 --> 00:32:58,720
to eat anything good back in college.

640
00:32:59,440 --> 00:33:01,770
I-I originally wanted to treat you alone,

641
00:33:03,060 --> 00:33:04,900
but I figured you wouldn't come.

642
00:33:04,970 --> 00:33:07,730
So, thanks to our classmates today,

643
00:33:08,950 --> 00:33:10,880
I finally got the chance to see you.

644
00:33:11,730 --> 00:33:13,280
Then you really were overthinking it.

645
00:33:13,280 --> 00:33:14,540
Don't do this again.

646
00:33:16,660 --> 00:33:17,730
Come on, everyone,

647
00:33:17,900 --> 00:33:19,700
I've created a group chat for us.

648
00:33:19,740 --> 00:33:21,290
Everyone, send your phone numbers there.

649
00:33:21,290 --> 00:33:23,990
Now we all use WeChat
and rarely call each other anymore.

650
00:33:23,990 --> 00:33:24,670
If someone's WeChat account
ever gets lost,

651
00:33:24,670 --> 00:33:25,710
we won't be able to reach them, right?

652
00:33:25,710 --> 00:33:27,120
Please pass me my phone.

653
00:33:28,070 --> 00:33:31,000
I just sent a red package in the group chat.
Go grab it!

654
00:33:32,560 --> 00:33:35,360
Whoever gets the biggest one
sends the next round.

655
00:33:35,900 --> 00:33:37,800
[Has everyone shared their phone number?]

656
00:33:37,820 --> 00:33:39,790
[Wang Ruohai]

657
00:33:41,510 --> 00:33:43,350
[Wang Ruohai]

658
00:33:50,260 --> 00:33:50,580
[Blocked Contacts]

659
00:33:51,400 --> 00:33:52,900
[Blocked Contacts]

660
00:33:54,640 --> 00:33:55,970
It really is God's will.

661
00:33:56,170 --> 00:33:58,240
Even my phone couldn't stand Wang Ruohai

662
00:33:58,240 --> 00:34:00,300
and automatically blacklisted him.

663
00:34:05,460 --> 00:34:07,060
Why did you blacklist me?

664
00:34:07,080 --> 00:34:09,260
Before, too many unimportant people
and things

665
00:34:09,260 --> 00:34:10,120
took up my time.

666
00:34:10,630 --> 00:34:12,630
Now I just want to clear them all out.

667
00:34:13,230 --> 00:34:15,030
So you don't even want to keep in touch?

668
00:34:15,030 --> 00:34:16,250
Even just as friends?

669
00:34:18,449 --> 00:34:20,179
I don't even want to be friends.

670
00:34:22,750 --> 00:34:23,610
I asked around.

671
00:34:24,270 --> 00:34:25,370
I know you're single now.

672
00:34:25,370 --> 00:34:26,719
That's why I went to all the trouble

673
00:34:26,719 --> 00:34:28,210
of organizing today's reunion.

674
00:34:28,210 --> 00:34:30,280
I'd already prepared myself for the worst.

675
00:34:30,280 --> 00:34:31,110
I just want to make it up to you.

676
00:34:31,110 --> 00:34:32,030
Don't bother.

677
00:34:33,320 --> 00:34:34,199
Look,

678
00:34:34,320 --> 00:34:36,250
aren't we both doing just fine now?

679
00:34:36,889 --> 00:34:37,880
To be honest,

680
00:34:38,030 --> 00:34:39,199
if it were the old me,

681
00:34:39,780 --> 00:34:42,730
I'd still want you
to feel guilty for the rest of your life.

682
00:34:42,730 --> 00:34:43,690
But now,

683
00:34:44,150 --> 00:34:45,639
I just want

684
00:34:45,670 --> 00:34:47,929
to be completely erased from your world.

685
00:34:52,500 --> 00:34:54,060
Before, when I had nothing,

686
00:34:55,280 --> 00:34:57,080
I thought the other half I needed

687
00:34:57,310 --> 00:34:59,850
was someone who could understand me,
be considerate of me,

688
00:34:59,850 --> 00:35:01,680
and even help me with my career.

689
00:35:02,080 --> 00:35:03,280
But now I've realized

690
00:35:04,060 --> 00:35:05,660
none of that really matters.

691
00:35:07,470 --> 00:35:10,600
What I truly want is someone
to share life's joys and hardships with.

692
00:35:10,600 --> 00:35:12,090
Being with someone I love

693
00:35:13,090 --> 00:35:14,950
matters more than anything else.

694
00:35:43,450 --> 00:35:45,110
Should I call my landlady?

695
00:35:46,840 --> 00:35:48,250
Is she asleep or not?

696
00:35:49,440 --> 00:35:50,550
It's been so many days.

697
00:35:50,550 --> 00:35:52,150
Why hasn't she contacted me?

698
00:35:52,950 --> 00:35:54,610
Why is she so stubborn?

699
00:35:55,480 --> 00:35:56,430
Is she mad at me,

700
00:35:56,430 --> 00:35:59,030
or has she simply
never thought about me at all?

701
00:36:38,210 --> 00:36:40,270
[Job Openings]

702
00:36:38,920 --> 00:36:40,500
I've finished my resume,

703
00:36:40,530 --> 00:36:42,560
but there isn't a single job
I want to apply for.

704
00:36:42,560 --> 00:36:43,860
It hasn't been that long.

705
00:36:43,860 --> 00:36:46,550
Taking a month or two
to find a job is perfectly normal.

706
00:36:46,550 --> 00:36:47,320
Take it easy.

707
00:36:47,880 --> 00:36:49,240
I used to be anxious

708
00:36:49,260 --> 00:36:51,320
because I had a mortgage to pay
and debts to clear.

709
00:36:51,320 --> 00:36:53,580
Now I'm anxious because I want to find out

710
00:36:53,590 --> 00:36:55,370
if there's actually a job out there,

711
00:36:55,370 --> 00:36:57,830
purely in finance,
that I'd genuinely like.

712
00:36:57,860 --> 00:37:00,300
Why don't you ask your tenant?

713
00:37:00,550 --> 00:37:02,350
He's in the same industry as you,

714
00:37:02,900 --> 00:37:04,510
and he has a lot of connections.

715
00:37:04,510 --> 00:37:05,710
Maybe he can help you.

716
00:37:07,090 --> 00:37:07,820
That's true.

717
00:37:08,880 --> 00:37:09,610
I'll ask him.

718
00:37:12,440 --> 00:37:14,360
[Pretentious Li]

719
00:37:13,680 --> 00:37:15,110
Our current equity structure

720
00:37:14,580 --> 00:37:17,860
[Fulaxida Equity Distribution]

721
00:37:15,130 --> 00:37:16,150
is still fairly well balanced.

722
00:37:16,150 --> 00:37:17,030
I have 34%,

723
00:37:17,050 --> 00:37:18,080
and you have 33%.

724
00:37:18,400 --> 00:37:19,590
Together,

725
00:37:19,590 --> 00:37:21,110
that's 67%,

726
00:37:21,110 --> 00:37:22,470
over the majority control threshold.

727
00:37:22,470 --> 00:37:23,570
What does that mean?

728
00:37:23,570 --> 00:37:24,770
It means we have complete authority

729
00:37:23,710 --> 00:37:25,740
[Fulaxida Equity Distribution]

730
00:37:24,800 --> 00:37:26,040
over major decisions

731
00:37:26,280 --> 00:37:28,470
like amending the company charter,
splitting or merging the company,

732
00:37:28,470 --> 00:37:29,630
changing business scope, and so on.

733
00:37:29,630 --> 00:37:30,670
But

734
00:37:30,840 --> 00:37:32,200
if we dilute our equity,

735
00:37:32,240 --> 00:37:33,710
even by just 1%—

736
00:37:33,760 --> 00:37:34,720
say,

737
00:37:34,120 --> 00:37:35,810
[Fulaxida Equity Distribution]

738
00:37:34,720 --> 00:37:35,990
down to 66%—

739
00:37:36,630 --> 00:37:39,160
we'd lose absolute control
and fall into relative control,

740
00:37:39,160 --> 00:37:40,860
where the threshold is just 51%.

741
00:37:40,860 --> 00:37:43,390
Past that point,
any major company decisions

742
00:37:43,550 --> 00:37:45,800
would need shareholder approval.

743
00:37:48,830 --> 00:37:49,650
Got it?

744
00:37:50,360 --> 00:37:51,490
Let it sink in first.

745
00:37:56,350 --> 00:37:58,370
[When will you be back
from your business trip?]

746
00:38:05,650 --> 00:38:06,980
I can't take it anymore.

747
00:38:07,090 --> 00:38:08,690
My brain's about to explode.

748
00:38:10,270 --> 00:38:10,930
[Don't know yet.]

749
00:38:13,430 --> 00:38:16,880
The business world is like a battlefield—
that's just how it is.

750
00:38:16,880 --> 00:38:18,140
Memorize it. Hurry up.

751
00:38:19,430 --> 00:38:20,790
[Don't know yet.]

752
00:38:21,450 --> 00:38:22,960
My fault. It's my fault.

753
00:38:23,280 --> 00:38:25,200
I shouldn't have given you
that stupid advice.

754
00:38:25,200 --> 00:38:27,110
I just shouldn't have contacted him first.

755
00:38:27,110 --> 00:38:28,260
At this point,

756
00:38:28,280 --> 00:38:30,680
if I still can't tell
he's been avoiding me,

757
00:38:30,720 --> 00:38:32,250
then I really must be blind.

758
00:38:39,430 --> 00:38:42,430
Majority control threshold, 67%.

759
00:38:48,020 --> 00:38:49,470
What about 51%?

760
00:38:50,510 --> 00:38:52,280
51% is...

761
00:38:53,400 --> 00:38:54,660
Don't look over there.

762
00:38:58,590 --> 00:39:00,190
I think I should just go farm.

763
00:39:06,030 --> 00:39:06,800
I'm tired.

764
00:39:11,720 --> 00:39:13,720
You haven't recovered from gastroenteritis.
Go rest.

765
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:14,740
I'll do it in a bit.

766
00:39:15,280 --> 00:39:16,550
I've been fine for ages.

767
00:39:16,550 --> 00:39:18,880
Didn't I help her with the birthday event?

768
00:39:20,030 --> 00:39:21,650
These notebooks are new as well.

769
00:39:21,650 --> 00:39:23,050
Send them to the kids too?

770
00:39:23,210 --> 00:39:24,540
And these clothes,

771
00:39:24,570 --> 00:39:25,510
along with that old computer.

772
00:39:25,510 --> 00:39:26,760
Pack them all up and send them.

773
00:39:26,760 --> 00:39:27,920
Xin You said

774
00:39:27,920 --> 00:39:29,990
the kids over there
really need these things.

775
00:39:29,990 --> 00:39:30,780
Okay.

776
00:39:33,460 --> 00:39:35,440
Then let's send this batch first.

777
00:39:35,630 --> 00:39:37,130
Later, we can ask our friends

778
00:39:37,130 --> 00:39:38,880
and coworkers to donate as well.

779
00:39:38,880 --> 00:39:41,150
We should be able to gather another batch.

780
00:39:41,150 --> 00:39:44,550
I alone can rally enough donations
to fill several truckloads.

781
00:39:44,550 --> 00:39:46,800
Yeah, you're the best at that.

782
00:39:47,630 --> 00:39:48,280
Of course.

783
00:39:49,030 --> 00:39:51,160
Anyway, there's strength in numbers.

784
00:39:51,250 --> 00:39:52,980
So, how's your exam prep going?

785
00:39:56,030 --> 00:39:57,630
I already listed all my exam prep books

786
00:39:57,630 --> 00:39:58,880
on Goofish.

787
00:40:00,200 --> 00:40:00,840
Why?

788
00:40:02,110 --> 00:40:04,110
You're not taking the exam anymore?

789
00:40:06,400 --> 00:40:08,470
I thought you were seriously
preparing for it since you quit your job.

790
00:40:08,470 --> 00:40:09,630
That's why I never asked.

791
00:40:09,630 --> 00:40:11,240
How could you just decide not to take it?

792
00:40:11,240 --> 00:40:12,030
See?

793
00:40:12,360 --> 00:40:14,510
I told you she'd react exactly like this.

794
00:40:14,510 --> 00:40:15,570
You knew all along?

795
00:40:17,650 --> 00:40:19,190
You guys really don't need to worry.

796
00:40:19,190 --> 00:40:21,390
It's a registration-based system now.

797
00:40:21,680 --> 00:40:22,470
In the past,

798
00:40:22,470 --> 00:40:24,110
any sponsor
could make over a million a year

799
00:40:24,110 --> 00:40:25,090
and rake in huge signing fees.

800
00:40:25,090 --> 00:40:26,200
Things are different now.

801
00:40:26,200 --> 00:40:27,070
Besides passing the exam,

802
00:40:27,070 --> 00:40:29,240
you can also get directly recommended
by an investment bank.

803
00:40:29,240 --> 00:40:30,470
You mean,

804
00:40:30,470 --> 00:40:31,800
once you join a new company,

805
00:40:31,800 --> 00:40:34,060
you'll have them recommend you instead?

806
00:40:35,710 --> 00:40:36,870
That's one option.

807
00:40:37,630 --> 00:40:39,300
But you really need to think it through.

808
00:40:39,300 --> 00:40:41,110
This kind of job isn't something
you can just find whenever you want.

809
00:40:41,110 --> 00:40:42,310
You've tried before.

810
00:40:43,030 --> 00:40:45,360
I can give you a research report
or something,

811
00:40:45,360 --> 00:40:47,880
but beyond that, I can't really help you
with other companies.

812
00:40:47,880 --> 00:40:48,610
Don't worry.

813
00:40:49,030 --> 00:40:51,450
This time, I'm fully prepared.

814
00:40:53,400 --> 00:40:54,660
The kid's all grown up.

815
00:40:55,430 --> 00:40:57,490
As long as you've thought it through.

816
00:40:59,450 --> 00:41:01,070
I still have a part-time job at the mall.

817
00:41:01,070 --> 00:41:03,560
This is almost done. You guys keep at it.
Gotta go.

818
00:41:03,560 --> 00:41:05,090
Your time management is...

819
00:41:05,470 --> 00:41:06,400
Hold on, hold on.

820
00:41:06,550 --> 00:41:06,920
What?

821
00:41:06,920 --> 00:41:08,780
Take the trash out on your way out.

822
00:41:10,360 --> 00:41:11,240
Remember to eat!

823
00:41:11,240 --> 00:41:12,280
-Okay.
-Your stomach isn't very good.

824
00:41:12,280 --> 00:41:13,470
I'll ask around for you on my way.

825
00:41:13,470 --> 00:41:14,550
Okay, okay, bye.

826
00:41:14,550 --> 00:41:16,150
Bye, be careful on your way.

827
00:41:19,020 --> 00:41:21,210
I didn't realize I had so many clothes.

828
00:41:22,320 --> 00:41:22,920
Let me see.

829
00:41:23,440 --> 00:41:24,320
When you get the chance,

830
00:41:24,320 --> 00:41:26,800
just pack up the clothes and shoes
you don't need

831
00:41:26,800 --> 00:41:28,510
and send them to me.

832
00:41:30,550 --> 00:41:31,800
Okay, hanging up.

833
00:41:33,430 --> 00:41:34,200
Dang.

834
00:41:34,920 --> 00:41:35,590
Auntie.

835
00:41:37,400 --> 00:41:38,990
We bumped into each other again.

836
00:41:38,990 --> 00:41:40,650
We really have a special bond.

837
00:41:40,990 --> 00:41:42,680
H-How's your stomach now?

838
00:41:42,950 --> 00:41:44,480
Are you feeling any better?

839
00:41:44,880 --> 00:41:47,610
With a body like mine,
I've long since recovered.

840
00:41:48,070 --> 00:41:48,840
Um...

841
00:41:49,920 --> 00:41:51,950
Our program won first prize.

842
00:41:52,230 --> 00:41:53,930
Did Jun tell you?

843
00:41:54,110 --> 00:41:54,990
He told me.

844
00:41:55,330 --> 00:41:57,260
I have to say, that day, I really...

845
00:41:58,110 --> 00:41:59,840
I really admired you.

846
00:42:00,110 --> 00:42:01,240
You were so sick,

847
00:42:01,240 --> 00:42:04,570
yet you still gave it everything you had.
It was so touching.

848
00:42:05,470 --> 00:42:06,990
I'm part of the team too.

849
00:42:07,400 --> 00:42:08,150
I couldn't let my condition

850
00:42:08,150 --> 00:42:10,010
affect you or the rest of the team.

851
00:42:10,360 --> 00:42:11,430
And I certainly couldn't let

852
00:42:11,430 --> 00:42:13,510
all the months Jun put into
preparing for the dance competition

853
00:42:13,510 --> 00:42:14,880
go unrewarded.

854
00:42:17,100 --> 00:42:19,790
That last part is
the most important, right?

855
00:42:20,670 --> 00:42:23,270
That's
what mattered most to you too, isn't it?

856
00:42:23,990 --> 00:42:25,230
You girl.

857
00:42:25,540 --> 00:42:27,540
Well, I'd better get going, Auntie.

858
00:42:30,090 --> 00:42:32,970
Come over when you have time.

859
00:42:33,000 --> 00:42:35,600
I'll make you
those shepherd's purse wontons.

860
00:42:35,630 --> 00:42:37,160
They're really delicious.

861
00:42:37,170 --> 00:42:38,800
Okay. I'll definitely come
and try them sometime.

862
00:42:38,800 --> 00:42:39,470
Okay.

863
00:42:39,470 --> 00:42:40,470
Goodbye, Auntie.

864
00:42:52,070 --> 00:42:53,660
[In the next episode
of "Love Has Fireworks"]

865
00:42:55,470 --> 00:42:57,110
What exactly do you want, Wang Ruohai?

866
00:42:56,180 --> 00:42:58,500
[Let's start over. Wang Ruohai]

867
00:42:57,630 --> 00:42:58,280
I just want you

868
00:42:58,280 --> 00:42:59,550
to unblock me.

869
00:42:59,960 --> 00:43:01,160
Looks like it worked.

870
00:43:02,150 --> 00:43:04,680
I had dinner
with some business partners yesterday

871
00:43:04,680 --> 00:43:06,210
and drank a little too much,

872
00:43:06,360 --> 00:43:08,020
so I didn't hear my phone ring.

873
00:43:08,400 --> 00:43:09,990
I just wanted to use this trip

874
00:43:09,990 --> 00:43:12,590
to really sort out
my thoughts once and for all.

875
00:43:12,800 --> 00:43:13,350
Look at me.

876
00:43:13,350 --> 00:43:14,340
Right now,

877
00:43:14,530 --> 00:43:15,090
tell me,

878
00:43:15,400 --> 00:43:16,490
how do you feel?

879
00:43:16,900 --> 00:43:18,710
All I ever think about is seeing her.

